  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Currently, when configuring `buidler-etherscan` plugin, the network api endpoint is a mandatory parameter:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  etherscan: {\r\n    url: \"https://api-rinkeby.etherscan.io/api\",\r\n    apiKey: ETHERSCAN_API_KEY,\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nI propose the following:\r\nMake the `url` parameter _optional_, and try to resolve the network (eg. ropsten, rinkeby etc.) from the _name_ of the network in the BRE. \r\n\r\nA call to:\r\n`yarn buidler verify-contract --name Example --network rinkeby --address 0x...`\r\n\r\nWould use the apropriate rinkeby url.\r\n\r\nProviding the url in config (or potentially as a task argument) would override the default.",
