    "body": "This is related to something I think could be improved for the etherscan plugin. I think the `url` field should accept a map of networks to urls, something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nurl: string | {[network: string]: string}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you pass a string, the same URL is used for all networks (which maybe doesn't make sense, but it would make it easier to use when you only care for one network). If not, the url is taken from the map using the selected network.\r\n\r\nIf this is implemented, then your issue is fixed by simply using a reasonable default value for the url.",
